article.headline: Eursher and Martin score 16 to lead Southeast Missouri State over Tennessee Tech 88-69
article.description: — Evan Eursher and Rob Martin both had 16 points in Southeast Missouri State's 88-69 victory against Tennessee Tech on Thursday night.
article.linkText: Eursher and Martin score 16 to lead Southeast Missouri State over Tennessee Tech 88-69
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- — Evan Eursher and Rob Martin both had 16 points in Southeast Missouri State's 88-69 victory against Tennessee Tech on Thursday night. Eursher shot 6 for 8, including 4 for 5 from beyond the arc for the Redhawks (8-16, 3-8 Ohio Valley Conference). Martin shot 6 for 13, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc. Josh Earley had 14 points and finished 7 of 10 from the floor. Josiah Davis led the Golden Eagles (7-17, 2-9) in scoring, finishing with 20 points. Tennessee Tech also got 14 points from Rodney Johnson Jr.. In addition, Diante Wood had 11 points. The loss is the sixth in a row for the Golden Eagles. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
